[SN]TITLE[SN]
Greece kids: 'We need more hope in our lives'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Greece has agreed to a new deal with the European Union to try and stop their money problems from getting any worse.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
13 July 2015 Last updated at 09:00 BST
The country is struggling with huge debts and it's affecting the lives of lots of people who live there, including many children.
Newsround reporter Ricky has been to Greece's capital city, Athens, to meet children and find out how things have changed for them.
He met up with Ioanis Pavlos and Stergios and their family to hear what life is like at the moment.
Guide: Why is Greece in so much trouble?
